This is a README for the first major project of the school my_printf project made by Matteo Maistre and Emilien Chinsy.

In this project we had to recreate the printf function in the most faithful way possible (up to the C99 standard).

if you wish for more information about the intricacies of printf, we recommend this website: https://cplusplus.com/reference/cstdio/printf/
it is very comprehensive and a lot easier to read than the man, it does say C++ reference but it is still up to date for C

the project files are seperated into different folders:
Makefile at the root which you can use to compile all our code into a library, you can use our code by compiling your main file using the -L and -l flags to get to our library and the -I flag to get to our my.h (which is located in src/includes/)

"src" will contain all the project files, in src there will be:
      my_printf at the root
      "Specifiers" which contains all the files that will be called for each specifier
      "Format_handling" which will contians the files for format handling
      "includes" which contains struct.h and my.h which contain respectively, the definition and creation of our array of function pointer containing the specifiers and their associated function

"tests" which will contain the files we use for testing, we run our tests with criterion.

